<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1876-05-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1876-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                        <head>No. 134.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Hoffman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-05-27"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 27,
                                1876</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your telegram received. Sir Edward Thornton has read to me one from Lord
                            Derby, stating that you had proposed to him the negotiation of the
                            additional article.</p>
                        <p>You will please inform me immediately whether the suggestion proceeded in
                            the first instance from you or from him, and if from him, how far you
                            may have encouraged it.</p>
                        <closer><signed>FISH, <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>